title: $A holding onto earlier gains
text:
Thu, Aug 20, 2015, 2:18 PM AEST - Australia Markets close in 1 hr 42 mins $A holding onto earlier gains AAP â€“ 1 hour 44 minutes ago Recommend Print 
The Australian dollar is flat, levelling off in morning trade after an up and down offshore session. 
At 1200 AEST on Thursday, the currency was trading at 73.52 US cents, a touch down from 73.53 cents on Wednesday. 
The currency steadily lost ground on Wednesday night on the back of falling commodity prices, but rallied as much as half a US cent after Federal Open Market Committee (FOMC) minutes showed there were doubts about the likelihood of an interest rate hike in September. 
KEY MOVEMENTS: 
* 73.52 US cents, from 73.53 cents on Wednesday 
* 91.13 Japanese yen, from 91.37 yen 
* 66.03 euro cents, from 66.45 euro cents 
* 111.31 New Zealand cents, from 111.56 NZ cents 
* 46.87 British pence, from 46.91 pence 
Government bond yields: 
* CGS 5.5pct Jan 2018, 1.861pct, from 1.901pct on Wednesday 
* CGS 4.25pct April 2026, 2.749pct, from 2.825pct 
Sydney Futures Exchange prices: 
* The September 2015 10-year bond futures contract was trading at 97.295 (implying a yield of 2.705 per cent), up from 97.225 (2.775 per cent) on Wednesday. 
* The September 2015 three-year bond futures contract was at 98.110 (2.890 per cent), up from 98.060 (1.940 per cent). 
(*Currency closes taken at 1700 AEST previous local session, bond market closes taken at 1630 AEST previous local session) 
Source: IRESS
